I have used a number of different apps to take notes in my University lectures and I like MetaMoji Note the best. This app is not perfect, but it is very near perfect. For reference, I am using a Samsung Galaxy Note 10.1 2014 Edition. This app works very well with the S-pen. The writing is extremely smooth and responsive, which is the most important feature for me. I love all of the other features of the app, but a few are missing and they are keeping me from giving a 5-star rating. Most importantly, there is no export to PDF feature. This is a huge pain, as you must use another app to create a pdf of the exported images. Other cons of the app include: no palm rejection (a major issue for large tablet users), no shape drawing (somewhat neutralized with the set of images that comes with the app), no support for non-MetaMoji cloud service backup, no option to change the default paper size and magnification ratio (mostly neutralized by the ability to create note templates). Another missing option is scrolling when using 2 fingers on the screen. Over all, this app is really good. I would rate 5 stars with PDF export and palm rejection.
